French President Emmanuel Macron and US President Donald Trump held a joint press conference during Trump's visit to Paris. Macron thanked Trump for accepting his invitation to attend the Bastille Day celebrations in France and emphasized the importance of the historic alliance between their two countries. The leaders discussed various topics including trade, terrorism, the situation in Iraq and Syria, and climate change. They expressed a shared determination to fight terrorism and work towards political solutions in the Middle East. On the issue of climate change, Macron reiterated his commitment to the Paris Accord while Trump stated that something could happen with regards to the US's position on the agreement. The press conference also touched on the recent controversy surrounding Trump's son's meeting with a Russian lawyer and Trump's previous comments about the safety of Paris. The leaders highlighted their willingness to work together and their mutual respect for each other.